<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910820-0020</DOCNO><DOCID>910820-0020.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Maxxam Inc.:   Unit Makes Exchange Offer   Of $170.9 Million in Notes</HL><DATE>08/20/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C21</SO><CO>   KLU MXM</CO><MS>BASIC MATERIALS (BSC)</MS><IN>ALUMINUM (ALU)BUYBACKS, REDEMPTIONS, SWAP OFFERS (BBK)ALL NON-FERROUS METALS (NFR)</IN><NS>BUYBACKS, REDEMPTIONS, REPURCHASES, SWAPS (BBK)</NS><RE>CALIFORNIA (CA)NORTH AMERICA (NME)PACIFIC RIM (PRM)TEXAS (TX)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   A Maxxam Inc. unit offered to exchange new secured notesmaturing in 1995 for $170.9 million in existing subordinatednotes maturing in 1992.   Maxxam Group Inc., an aluminum and forest-productsconcern, said it made the exchange offer in a Securities andExchange Commission filing. The exchange offer covers $140million in subordinated notes of Maxxam Group and $30.9million in notes of its Houston-based parent, which also hasreal estate interests.</LP><TEXT>   The company said the offer covers Maxxam Group's 13 5/8%senior subordinated notes due May 15, 1992, and Maxxam's 141/4% senior subordinated notes due Aug. 1, 1992. The newnotes would be secured by a pledge of outstanding commonshares of Maxxam Group's Kaiser Aluminum Corp. unit.   Under the terms of the company's offer, holders couldexchange each $1,000 in principal amount of existing notesfor $10 in cash and either $1,000 in principal amount of new12 1/4% senior secured notes from Maxxam Group or $1,000 inprincipal amount of new senior secured floating-rate notesfrom the unit.   The company said the dealer managers for the exchangeoffer are Donaldson, Lufkin andamp; Jenrette Securities Corp. andBear, Stearns andamp; Co.</TEXT></DOC>